Description: Bronze spear-butt with two prongs joined by a flat cross-piece.
Curator's comments: This object appears to be shown on pl. III, top row, third from the left, W.M.F. Petrie, 'Tanis II, Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes)' (Egypt Exploration Fund, Memoirs 4; 1888). Unfortunately, there is no tomb number above writtne above it, only '?'.
